1 February 2021 Government would like to advise the public about details pertaining to the Special Official Funeral of the late Justice Khayelihle Kenneth Mthiyane.  Justice Mthiyane passed on Thursday, 28 January 2021.  Following his passing, President Ramaphosa has honoured him by designating his funeral as a Special Official Funeral, Category 2. 1.    FuneralThe Special Official Funeral Service of Justice Mthiyane will be held at Natal Sharks Board in Durban, KZN  on Wednesday, 03 February starting from 09h00. Justice Mthiyane will be laid to rest on the same day at Redhill Cemetery in Durban . In keeping with the COVD-19 Alert Level 3 lockdown protocols currently in place, the number of funeral attendees will be kept to the maximum of 50 people. Government encourages all  mourners who may not be able to physically attend the funeral to follow the proceedings on the following online platforms: @GovernmentZAFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/GovernmentZA(link is external) Twitter: http://twitter.com/GovernmentZA(link is external) YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/user/GovernmentZA(link is external) The official hashtag is #RIPJusticeMthiyane 2. Messages of Condolence Messages of condolence to the family and friends of the late Justice Mthiyane may be sent to the following email address and online tribute pages: condolences@gcis.gov.za(link sends e-mail),  https://www.gov.za/JusticeMthiyane  or  https://www.facebook.com/Gov.... Enquiries:Phumla Williams, GCIS Director-GeneralCell: 083 5010 139 Issued by: Government Communication and Information System